      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's not always outright warfare, but the deep-seated nature of these loyalties makes political cooperation extremely difficult. While some local cooperation exists, the national political structure often exacerbates ethnic divisions for power grabs. For NGOs, working across these lines requires immense sensitivity, as any perceived favoritism toward one group can trigger backlash from others. The cycle of violence is often perpetuated by political elites exploiting these existing lines of division.",
      "source": "target",
